==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hobsons choice
<hw>Hob"son's choice"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A choice without an
alternative; the thing offered or nothing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is said to have had its origin in the name of one
<xex>Hobson</xex>, at Cambridge, England, who let horses, and required
every customer to take in his turn the horse which stood next the stable
door.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hocco</ent>⟦br⟧
